The paper deals with the behavior of a tatonnement price update rule in ongoing Fisher markets, which is a topic in computational game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC). The paper also involves analyzing the convergence of the update rule, which requires techniques from dynamical systems (cs.DS). The use of CES utilities and the characterization of nested CES utilities suggest a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
